{/* Additional Project Description Section */}

Project Overview

Our project leverages state-of-the-art deep learning techniques to classify brain MRI images, facilitating early diagnosis and treatment of dementia-related conditions.

Dataset

We have explored Kaggle's diverse brain image datasets, encompassing classes like ‘Non Demented’, ‘Very Mild Demented’, ‘Mild Demented’, and ‘Moderate Demented’. This comprehensive dataset is essential for training our models effectively.

Methodology

  • Implemented Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) using TensorFlow and Keras for image classification.
  • Conducted rigorous exploratory data analysis (EDA), including visualizing random images and scrutinizing their dimensions.
  • Employed data preprocessing techniques such as normalization and caching for efficient processing.
  • Applied data augmentation techniques to enhance model generalization.

Future Steps

Future steps include refining preprocessing techniques, optimizing data visualizations, and experimenting with hyperparameters for further model enhancement.
